      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk 5: Resource Misuse"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An agent optimising for task completion may acquire far more resources than the task requires \u2014 making excessive API calls, storing unnecessary data, or spinning up cloud infrastructure that persists after the task ends. Resource misuse has direct cost implications and can also create privacy violations if the agent retains data it shouldn't."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, time\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n@dataclass\nclass ResourceBudget:\n    \"\"\"Hard caps on resource consumption per agent task.\"\"\"\n    max_tool_calls: int = 50\n    max_api_calls: int = 20\n    max_tokens_spent: int = 50_000\n    tool_call_count: int = field(default=0, init=False)\n    api_call_count: int = field(default=0, init=False)\n    tokens_spent: int = field(default=0, init=False)\n\n    def check_tool_call(self, name: str) -> None:\n        self.tool_call_count += 1\n        if self.tool_call_count > self.max_tool_calls:\n            raise RuntimeError(\n                f\"Tool call budget exceeded ({self.max_tool_calls} max). \"\n                f\"Last attempted: {name}\"\n            )\n\n    def check_api_call(self, tokens_used: int) -> None:\n        self.api_call_count += 1\n        self.tokens_spent += tokens_used\n        if self.api_call_count > self.max_api_calls:\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"API call budget exceeded ({self.max_api_calls} max)\")\n        if self.tokens_spent > self.max_tokens_spent:\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Token budget exceeded ({self.max_tokens_spent} max)\")\n\n\ndef budgeted_agent_loop(task: str, tools: list[dict], budget: ResourceBudget) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Run an agent loop that enforces hard resource budgets.\"\"\"\n    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": task}]\n\n    for _ in range(budget.max_api_calls):\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            tools=tools,\n            messages=messages,\n        )\n\n        budget.check_api_call(response.usage.input_tokens + response.usage.output_tokens)\n\n        if response.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n            return response.content[0].text if response.content else \"\"\n\n        tool_results = []\n        for block in response.content:\n            if block.type == \"tool_use\":\n                budget.check_tool_call(block.name)\n                tool_results.append({\n                    \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                    \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                    \"content\": f\"executed {block.name}\",\n                })\n\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n\n    return \"Budget exhausted before task completion\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk 6: Trust Chain Violations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In multi-agent systems, a hierarchy of agents passes context and instructions between them. Each layer in the hierarchy should receive only the authority it needs \u2014 but implementations frequently violate this by passing full system prompts, unfiltered tool results, or over-broad credentials down the chain."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The trust chain problem has two directions:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Downward violation: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the orchestrator grants a sub-agent more permissions than the sub-agent's task requires. A summarisation sub-agent does not need write access to the database."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Upward violation: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "a sub-agent or tool result is treated as having the trust level of the operator. Content returned by a tool should never be interpreted as a system-level directive."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The rule of thumb: a sub-agent should receive a minimal system prompt that describes only its specific sub-task, a minimal tool list, and credentials scoped to its sub-task. It should not receive the full orchestrator system prompt or the orchestrator's credentials."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef run_sub_agent(\n    sub_task: str,\n    sub_tools: list[dict],\n    sub_system_prompt: str,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run a sub-agent with a purpose-built system prompt and minimal tool set.\n    Never pass the orchestrator's system prompt or credentials to sub-agents.\n    \"\"\"\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        system=sub_system_prompt,  # scoped, not the full orchestrator prompt\n        tools=sub_tools,            # minimal, task-specific\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": sub_task}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text if response.content else \"\"\n\n\ndef orchestrator(user_task: str, all_tools: list[dict]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Orchestrator that delegates sub-tasks with minimal authority.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Step 1: summarise (read-only sub-agent)\n    summary = run_sub_agent(\n        sub_task=f\"Summarise the key points in: {user_task}\",\n        sub_tools=[t for t in all_tools if t[\"name\"] in {\"read_file\", \"search\"}],\n        sub_system_prompt=\"You are a summarisation assistant. Read files and produce summaries. Do not modify anything.\",\n    )\n\n    # Step 2: act on summary (write sub-agent, separate credentials)\n    action = run_sub_agent(\n        sub_task=f\"Based on this summary, update the status report: {summary}\",\n        sub_tools=[t for t in all_tools if t[\"name\"] in {\"write_file\"}],\n        sub_system_prompt=\"You are a report writer. Write only to files under reports/. Do not read sensitive files.\",\n    )\n\n    return action\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk Interaction: Injection Enables Scope Creep"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "These risks are not independent. A successful prompt injection can exploit scope creep: injected instructions tell the agent its scope has expanded, and the agent's optimiser dutifully pursues the injected goal because goal misgeneralisation makes it unable to distinguish a legitimate scope expansion from an injected one. This interaction means mitigating one risk does not automatically mitigate the other \u2014 both need independent defences."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent-specific risks are distinct from classical LLM safety concerns because they arise from the combination of tool use, multi-step planning, and real-world side-effects. The six principal risks are prompt injection (adversarial content in the environment), compounding errors (wrong decisions cascade), scope creep (literal goal optimisation exceeds intent), irreversible actions (side-effects cannot be undone), resource misuse (excessive acquisition), and trust chain violations (sub-agents receive excess authority). Each risk requires a purpose-built mitigation: input sanitisation, step verification, explicit scope constraints, HITL checkpoints before irreversible calls, resource budgets, and minimal-authority sub-agent design."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
